{
  "texts": [
    "Any overlap of the observed wavelengths (e.g.",
    "for a broad band) with emission lines, especially broad lines that are known to undergo microlensing as well, could contaminate the measured flux ratios.",
    "The extent of the chromatic variation and the level of the no-microlensing baseline, which are known to affect source measurements (Bate et al. 2018), could also play a role for measuring κ *, but this has not been investigated yet.",
    "Finally, there are cases where the flux ratio data are simply not sufficient to lead to any conclusive κ * results foot_16 (e.g.",
    "Bate et al. 2008; Floyd et al. 2009)."
  ]
}